'''Austrian heraldry''' are the armorial bearings (known as armory) and other heraldic symbols once used by the [[Austrian people|Austrian]] [[Austrian monarchy|monarchy]]. They are closely related to [[German heraldry]], as [[Austria]] is a [[Germanophone]] country, but it show some particularities of their own, partly due to the mutual influence to and from the lands of the former [[Habsburg monarchy]].

