{{unreferenced|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox company | name = Egyptian Natural Gas Company (GASCO) | logo = Gasco.gif | logo_size = 220px | caption = | type = | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 1997 | founder = [[Egyptian_Natural_Gas_Holding_Company]](EGAS) | defunct = | location_city = [[New Cairo]] | location_country = [[Egypt]] | location = | locations = Egypt,Jordan,Lebanon | area_served = | key_people = | industry = [[Natural Gas transmission & Processing]] | products = Sales gas, Propane, Ethean/Propane mixture, LPG and Condensates | services = Delivering Natural Gas to Power Sector, Iron & steel, Cements, Heavy Industries and Industrial Areas in General. | revenue = 6 billion [[Egyptian pound|ج.م]] | operating_income = | net_income = 1.8 billion [[Egyptian pound|ج.م]] | aum = | assets = | equity = | owner = Egyptian Government | num_employees = 4500+ | parent = [[ Ministry of petroleum (egypt)]] | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = [http://www.gasco.com.eg/ www.gasco.com.eg] | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Egyptian Natural Gas Company (GASCO)''' is a subsidiary of the [[Egyptian_Natural_Gas_Holding_Company]] operating in the field of natural gas transmission, distribution and processing. The company was established in March 1997. GASCO operates the gas grid with total length of {{convert|22000|km}}. The national gas grid has extended to neighboring countries through the [[Arab Gas Pipeline]].
The main shareholder is the Egyptian Holding Company for Natural Gas with 70% of shares. Petrojet and Egypt Gas own 15% of shares both.
