{{Infobox Submarine communications cable | cable_name = FARICE-1 | owners = [[Farice]] | map = FARICE-1-map.png | caption = ''Red is submarine, Blue is terrestrial, now extended to London''. | landing_points = {{ordered list | item1_value=1 | 1 = [[Seyðisfjörður]], [[Iceland]] | item2_value=3 | 2 = [[Funningsfjørður]], [[Faroe Islands]] | item3_value=5 | 3 = [[Dunnet Bay]], [[Caithness]], [[Highland (council area)|Highland]], [[Scotland]] }} | design_capacity = 720{{nbsp}}Gbit/s | current_capacity = 11{{nbsp}}Tbit/s | length = {{convert|1205|km|mi}} | first_use_date = {{Start date|2004|01}} }}
'''FARICE-1''' is a [[submarine communications cable]] connecting [[Iceland]], the [[Faroe Islands]] and [[Scotland]]. The cable has been in use since January 2004 without a fault and is 100% owned by [http://www.farice.is/about-us/shareholders/ Icelandic shareholders]. {{fact|date=October 2015}} The cable had an initial design capacity of 720 Gbit/s and is a two fibre pair design. The length of the cable is 1205 km for the direct route between Iceland and Scotland. The cable structure and repeaters were made by Pirelli and the terminal equipment was supplied by TYCO. In the year 2013 the terminal equipment was [http://www.farice.is/media-center/press-releases/nr/327 upgraded by Ciena] (100Gbit/s technology) bringing the total capacity of the submarine cable to 11 Tbit/s. The cable has service access points in Reykjavik and [http://verneglobal.com Keflavik Airport] as well as in London Telehouse East. The company [[Farice|Farice ehf]] sells services over the FARICE-1 cable. FARICE-2 was never built. [[Danice|DANICE]] is the complementary submarine cable.
The [[cable landing point|landing points]] are: * 1. [[Seyðisfjörður]], Iceland, [[Backhaul (telecommunications)|backhauled]] to Reykjavík and KEF Airport * 3. [[Funningsfjørður]], Faroe Islands, backhauled to 4. [[Tórshavn]] * 5. [[Dunnet Bay]], [[Caithness]], [[Highland (council area)|Highland]], Scotland, backhauled to London Telehouse (previously Edinburgh)
==See also== *[[DANICE]] *[[SHEFA-2]] *[[Greenland Connect]] *[[CANTAT-3]]
