{{about|the defunct German Familienbuch|Ortsfamilienbuch|One-place study}}
A '''Familienbuch''' ({{IPA-de|faˈmiːli̯ənˌbuːx|lang}}, "Family-book") was a [[family register]], a [[Genealogy|genealogical summary]] that was issued in Germany by the local [[civil registry]] upon [[marriage]] and contained data on [[birth]], marriage and [[death]] of the couple as well as the birth data of any children stemming for this marriage.

Since January 1, 2009, ''Familienbücher'' have no longer been issued.

