'''Fear Doirche''', meaning literally the ''Dark Man'' in [[Irish language|Irish]]. A malevolent [[fairy]], the chief agent of mortal abduction, usually in the service of a fairy queen. Very few that are taken by him to [[fairy|fairy land]], or the [[Aos Sí|sidhe]] ([[Celtic Mythology]]), ever return to tell the tale.<ref>{{cite book|last=MacKillop|first=James|title=Celtic Mythology|year=2000|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=0-19-280120-1|page=205}}</ref> In Irish mythology he belongs with the [[Tuatha D&#233; Danann]] and is prominent in such tales in the [[Fenian Cycle]] as The ''Birth of Ois&#237;n''.<ref>{{cite book|last=Stephens|first=James|title=Irish Fairy Tales|year=1920}}</ref>
