The '''Japan Intellectual Property Association''' ('''JIPA''') is a [[non-profit]], [[non-governmental organization]] representing "industries and users of the [[intellectual property]] (IP) system".<ref name="intro">JIPA web site, [http://www.jipa.or.jp/english/what/index.html ''Introduction'']. Consulted on May 1, 2009.</ref> It was established in 1938.<ref>Katsunosuke Maeda, [https://web.archive.org/web/20060721175209/http://www.jipa.or.jp/content/english/journal/vol1_01/2001_1_01.pdf ''Introductory Greetings on the Publication of the Founding Edition of the “Journal of JIPA”. On the Founding Issue of the “Journal of JIPA”''], Journal of JIPA, Vol.1 No.1 2001, p. 2. The Internet Archive, archived on July 21, 2006.</ref> It claims to be the largest private organization in [[Japan]] concerned with intellectual property rights,<ref>Katsunosuke Maeda, ''Introductory Greetings on the Publication of the Founding Edition of the “Journal of JIPA”. On the Founding Issue of the “Journal of JIPA”'', Journal of JIPA, Vol.1 No.1 2001, p. 3.</ref> with more than one thousand members as of 2009.<ref name="intro"/>
