'''Jueces de Castilla''' (English: Judges of Castile) are two legendary figures of the [[County of Castile]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.diariodeleon.es/noticias/revista/jueces-castilla_1201288.html|title=Los jueces de Castilla|website=Diariodeleon.es|language=es|accessdate=31 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.condadodecastilla.es/leyendas/la-leyenda-de-los-jueces-de-castilla/|title=La leyenda de los Jueces de Castilla - Historia del Condado de Castilla|date=20 October 2015|website=Condadodecastilla.es|language=es|accessdate=31 December 2017}}</ref> chosen by primitive Castilians to avoid the implementation of [[liber iudiciorum]] by Leonese court. It was based on local custumary law or [[fazañas]].

