{{Infobox Union |name= LAB |country= [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque Country]] |affiliation= [[World Federation of Trade Unions]] |members= 45,000 |full_name= Nationalist/Patriotic Workers' Committees |native_name= Langile Abertzaleen Batzordeak |image= [[File:LAB-Sindikatua.jpg|180px]] |founded= 1974 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Bilbao]] |people= [[Garbiñe Aranburu]], general secretary |website= [http://www.lab.eus/eu/hasiera lab.eus] |footnotes= }} '''''Langile [[Abertzale]]en Batzordeak''''' ('''LAB,''' [[Basque language|Basque]] for '''"Nationalist Workers' Committees"''') is a [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque]] [[left-wing nationalism|left-wing nationalist]] and [[separatism|separatist]] [[trade union]]<ref>{{Citation |first=José M. |last=Faraldo |title=Spain: The Common Experience of Transition and a Military Coup |work=Solidarity with Solidarity: Western European Trade Unions and the Polish Crisis, 1980–1982 |publisher=Lexington Books |year=2010 |page=54}}</ref> operating mainly in Spain currently led by [[Garbiñe Aranburu]].
It was created in 1974 by [[Jon Idigoras]] among others. They are part of the [[Basque National Liberation Movement]], an aggregation of leftist [[Basque nationalist]] forces including the illegal paramilitary organization [[Euskadi Ta Askatasuna]] (ETA) and the illegal parties [[Batasuna]] and [[Segi (organization)|Segi]]. It is supported by around 45.000 affiliates.<ref>[http://www.gara.net/paperezkoa/20120617/347429/es/LAB-sera-pilar-fundamental-cambios-politicos-sociales 'LAB será un pilar fundamental en los cambios políticos y sociales'], Gara, June 17, 2012</ref>
The union is legal and it is one of the four major of its kind in the Basque Country. In the last decades it has been working mostly with the other nationalist union, [[Basque Workers' Solidarity|ELA]], while both have been opposed often by the Spanish-wide trade unions, [[Unión General de Trabajadores|UGT]] and [[CC.OO.]], that make up their own bloc.
In 2011 it had the 16.2%<ref>http://www.labsindikatua.org/es/sindicato-lab/101-hauteskunde-sindikalak/641-lab-izan-da-2011-urtean-hego-euskal-herrian-ordezkaritza-gehien-igo-duen-sindikatua-</ref> of the labor delegates in the [[Southern Basque Country]].
