The '''Moogouei''' (Persian: '''[[:fa:موگویی|موگویی]]''') clan is one of the six clans that form the [[Chahar Lang]] branch of the [[Bakhtiari people|Bakhtiari]] people in western [[Iran]].

[[Category:Bakhtiari people]]
[[Category:Ethnic groups in Iran]]

{{Asia-ethno-group-stub}}
{{Iran-stub}}

{{Refimprove|date=August 2010}}
{{Copts}}  {{Religion in Egypt}}
There are more than 300,000 Protestants in Egypt, with 250,000 being members of the [[Evangelical Church of Egypt (Synod of the Nile)|Evangelical Church of Egypt]], 75,000 [[Pentecostals]], and various other [[Protestants]] scattered in smaller denominations.

==List of Protestant denominations==
*The [[Evangelical Church of Egypt (Synod of the Nile)|Evangelical Church of Egypt]]
*[[Assemblies of God]] (75,000 adherents)
*[[Free Methodist]] (120 churches, 20,000 members)
*[[Christian Brethren]] (15,000 adherents)
*The [[Episcopal Church in Jerusalem and the Middle East]] (a member of the [[Anglican Communion]];  between 10,000 and 15,000 members in Egypt){{Citation needed |date=February 2014}}
*[[Pentecostal Church of God]] (3,775 adherents)
*[[Baptist|Egyptian Baptist Convention]] (2,250 members)
*[[Pentecostal Holiness Church]] (1,400 adherents)
*[[Church of God of Prophecy]] (1,100 adherents)
*[[Seventh-day Adventist Church]] (852 members)<ref>{{Citation | contribution-url = http://www.adventistatlas.org/viewCountry.asp?CtryCode=EG | contribution = Egypt | title = Adventist Atlas}}.</ref>

