{{Infobox prepared food | name = Serbian salad | image = | caption = | alternate_name = | country = [[Serbia]] | region = | creator = | course = | type = [[Salad]] | served = | main_ingredient = [[Tomato]]es, [[cucumber]]s, [[onion]]s, [[olive oil]], salt, [[feferon]] | variations = | calories = | other = }} '''Serbian salad''' is a [[vegetable]] [[salad]], usually served during summer with roast meat and other dishes.<ref name= "balkan">{{cite news |last=Lončar |first=Zorica |url= https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2017/06/serbian-delicacies.html |title=Balkan Guide: 10 Serbian Delicacies You Must Try |work=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]] |date=June 30, 2017 |accessdate=July 3, 2017}}</ref> It is made from diced fresh [[tomato]]es, [[cucumber]] and [[onion]]s, usually seasoned with [[sunflower oil]] or [[olive oil]], salt and commonly with a variety of [[hot pepper]] similar to [[cayenne pepper]] and called ''feferon''.
