{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox film | name = The Gifts | image = | caption = | director = | producer = [[Robert McBride (producer)|Robert McBride]] | writer = | narrator = [[Lorne Greene]] | music = [[Skitch Henderson]] | cinematography = | editing = | distributor = | released = {{film date|1970}} | runtime = 28 minutes | country = United States | language = English }} '''''The Gifts''''' is a 1970 American [[short film|short]] [[documentary film]] about [[water pollution]] in the United States. The film was produced by [[Robert McBride (producer)|Robert McBride]] for the [[United States Environmental Protection Agency]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nepis.epa.gov/Exe/ZyPURL.cgi?Dockey=910140N7.txt |title=Films from EPA |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=1977 |publisher=United States Environmental Protection Agency |location=Washington, D.C. |id=Brochure. EPA 905-F-77-002}}</ref> It was nominated for an [[Academy Award]] for [[Academy Award for Best Documentary (Short Subject)|Best Documentary Short]].<ref name="Oscars1971">{{Cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1971 |title=The 43rd Academy Awards (1971) Nominees and Winners |accessdate=July 4, 2015 |work=oscars.org |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150702005544/http://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1971 |archivedate=July 2, 2015 |df= }}</ref>
